data.meta_description: Tiberius was Roman Emperor, the son of Tiberius Claudius Nero and Livia Drusilla. His mother divorced Nero and married Augustus, making him a step-son of Octavian. He would later marry Augustus' daughter Julia the Elder and even later be adopted by Augustus, by which act he officially became a Julian, bearing the name Tiberius Julius Caesar. He was the stepson of Augustus, grand-uncle of Caligula, paternal uncle of Claudius, and great-grand uncle of Nero.
